article.description: Samajae Haynes-Jones tallied 10 points and 10 rebounds to carry Wichita State to a 63-55 win over Clemson in the second round of the NIT on Sunday.
article.headline: Haynes-Jones carries Wichita St. past Clemson 63-55 in NIT
article.linkText: Haynes-Jones carries Wichita St. past Clemson 63-55 in NIT
article.story: CLEMSON, S.C. -- In a story March 24 about an NIT game between Wichita State and Clemson, The Associated Press reported erroneously that Wichita State's next game is Thursday night. Wichita State's next game is Tuesday night, not Thursday night. A corrected version of the story is below: Haynes-Jones carries Wichita St. past Clemson 63-55 in NIT Samajae Haynes-Jones records 10 points and 10 rebounds to carry Wichita State to a 63-55 win over Clemson in the second round of the NIT CLEMSON, S.C. -- Samajae Haynes-Jones tallied 10 points and 10 rebounds to carry Wichita State to a 63-55 win over Clemson in the second round of the NIT on Sunday. Jaime Echenique had 18 points and three blocks for Wichita State (21-14), which has reached 20 wins in 10 straight seasons. Markis McDuffie added 16 points. Dexter Dennis had nine points, 11 rebounds and three blocks for the road team. Wichita State plays top-seeded Indiana on Tuesday night in the quarterfinals. The Tigers' 28.3 field-goal percentage represented the worst mark by a Wichita State opponent this season. Marcquise Reed had 18 points for the Tigers (20-14). Elijah Thomas added eight rebounds. David Skara had three blocks. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap , using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
